  "title": "Profiling Serverless Handlers Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide covers the process of profiling serverless functions utilizing FastAPI and Python 3.12+, offering insights into execution time and function calls for improved performance.",

  "key_points": [
    "Set up a FastAPI application with required dependencies.",
    "Implement the serverless handler within the FastAPI application.",
    "Enable profiling using Python's built-in cProfile module or external tools like Line_Profiler.",
    "Analyze and interpret the generated profile data to optimize your function's performance.",
    "Deploy the updated FastAPI application on a serverless platform (e.g., AWS Lambda, Google Cloud Functions, etc.)."
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nimport cProfile\nimport pstats\napp = FastAPI()\ndef profile(func):\n    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n        pr = cProfile.Profile()\n        pr.enable()\n        result = func(*args, **kwargs)\n        pr.disable()\n        s = pstats.Stats(pr)\n        s.sort_stats('cumulative').print_stats(20)\n        return result\n@app.get('/')\n@profile\ndef index():\n    ...\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    app.run()``"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for improved performance and profiling features.",
    "FastAPI v0.73.0 or later is recommended for compatibility with Python 3.12."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Profiling serverless functions incurs additional costs, so it's crucial to optimize your function before deploying it.",
    "The cProfile module can impact the performance of your application when profiling is enabled. Use it sparingly and during development cycles.",
    "Line_Profiler offers more granular insights into the execution time of individual lines of code."
  ]
